## Load dataset penguins.
penguins <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/APM3030/STA553/main/data/w02-penguins(1).csv"
penguins <- read_csv(penguins)

# Filter Penguins Dataset.
penguins_hw2 <- penguins %>%
# Exclude Missing Variables
na.exclude() %>%
# Filter by Adelie and Gentoo from Bisco and Torgersen Islands with a body mass less than 5000 and greater than 3500.
filter(species == "Adelie"|species == "Gentoo", island == "Biscoe"|island == "Torgersen", body_mass_g < 5000 & body_mass_g > 3500) %>% 
# Create new variable BMI
mutate(BMI = body_mass_g / 4000) %>% 
# Exclude variables X, sex, year, and body_mass_g.
select(-...1, -sex, -year, -body_mass_g)


# Theme for plots.

hw2.theme <- function() {
theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0),
        legend.key = element_rect(fill = "grey95"),
        legend.title = element_text(color = "darkred"))
}

download.file(myurl,z,mode="wb")

#create scatter plot
ggplot(data = penguins, mapping = aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = flipper_length_mm, color = species)) + 
geom_point(mapping = aes(size = body_mass_g, shape = island), alpha = 0.5) + 
geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = flipper_length_mm), method = "lm", se = FALSE)+   
  scale_color_manual(values=c("#E69F00", "#009E73","#CC79A7")) +
  labs(x = "Bill Length", y = "Flipper Length" , color = "Species :" , size = "Body Mass Grams :" , shape = "Island :" , title = "Association Between Bill Length and Flipper Length") +
  theme_light() +
  hw2.theme() +
  annotation_raster(raster.penguin, 30, 36, 210, 235) +
  annotate(geom="text" , 
                       x=43, 
                       y=173,
                       label=paste("Mean Body Mass",                          
                       round( penguins %>%
                       na.exclude %>% 
                       filter(species == "Adelie") %>%
                       summarise_at(vars(body_mass_g), list(name = mean)), digits = 0)), 
                       size = 3,
                       color = "#E69F00") +

                       x=42.5,

Looking at both charts, we can see a positive correlation between Bill Length and Flipper Length for each species. When filtering by weight, we see a less strong positive correlation.
The first chart shows Adelie penguins are from all three islands, Gentoo are from only the Biscoe island, and Chinstrap are from the Dream Island. Reviewing the second chart we can see Adelie Penguins have smaller flipper and bill lengths compared to Gentoo Penguins. We also can see the mean BMI of Adelie penguins is smaller than Gentoo penguiins when weight is filtered between 3500 and 5000 grams.
